I don&#x27;t think you&#x27;ve seen truly great async support, it&#x27;s virtually indistinguishable from sync code.<p>Sync:<p><pre><code>  let file = File.Open(&quot;foo.txt&quot;)
  let data = file.Read(8192)
  // Do some compute stuff with data</code></pre>
ASync:<p><pre><code>  let! file = File.OpenAsync(&quot;foo.txt&quot;)
  let! data = file.ReadAsync(8192)  
  // Do some compute stuff with data</code></pre>
